sql:
SELECT COUNT(test_id) AS count_of_low_complexity_successes
FROM test_cases
WHERE outcome = 'OK' AND complexity = 'low';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_test_cases
FROM test_cases
WHERE run_time > (
    SELECT AVG(run_time) 
    FROM test_cases
);

external_knowledge:
- "Passed" refers to test cases with a status of 'passed'; 
- "Top 10 longest-running test cases" refers to the 10 test cases with the highest runtime; 
- "Software versions" and "test environments" are represented by their respective names.
